cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper deals with training deep neural networks for image estimation tasks such as compressive-sensing and image restoration. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses unsupervised learning, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for image estimation involves exploiting domain-specific image statistics, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with measurement models, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper evaluates its method for compressive-sensing and blind deconvolution, which are topics in multimedia (cs.MM).
